ults in relatively short time spans, and suggests that high resolution\nnon-longitudinally averaged photospheric velocity residual measurements could\nbe produced to compare with coronal results, and to provide other diagnostics\nof the solar dynamo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jan 2017 18:39:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-15"}
